gw.api.admin

Class RegionSearchCriteria

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.admin.RegionSearchCriteria
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class RegionSearchCriteria
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Stores a user's search criteria when searching for regions. Currently the only criteria the user can specify are the region name and type.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      IQueryBeanResult<Bean> performSearch()
      Return a query processor that will yield all regions matching the current criteria. Null criteria are ignored. So, for example, if name is set but not type then the query processor will return all regions with the given name, regardless of type.

      The name criteria is a "starts with" match, so "So" or "Sou" will match "South CA". The type must match exactly.
      void setRegionName(String regionName)
